item.title: Wtf?
item.dc:creator: @Fridder Fridder
item.description:
@Fridder wrote:

Free Sosa:

But I have a dynamic IP so if I were to put my IP in the files it would change… which means id have to keep on compiling and uploading all the time,…

Which is why you would do this tutorial: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,403207.0.html
And change your IP at No-IP.com.

item.title: Wtf?
item.dc:creator: @Fridder Fridder
item.description:
@Fridder wrote:

192.168.1.74 is your IPv4 address… Only you and other people on your network can use it. You have to follow a portforwarding guide (if you have not already done so). After that, you put your IP address in the client’s files.
